vote, you make a decision, but it causes a lawsuit.

00:53:24.620 --> 00:53:25.820
If you lose,

00:53:25.900 --> 00:53:32.060
the district is responsible for paying. You are not you're individually held harmless from a personal liability.

00:53:32.780 --> 00:53:36.380
So the board is sued, and unfortunately, it happens all all the time,

00:53:37.995 --> 00:53:42.555
but and if there's a loss or even if there's a suit,

00:53:42.875 --> 00:53:46.395
your legal expenses are covered because it's the board getting sued.

00:53:47.035 --> 00:53:52.635
You don't have to worry about that. You don't have to worry about put should I put my house in my spouse's name so it doesn't get taken or something?

00:53:53.890 --> 00:53:54.610
However,

00:53:55.490 --> 00:54:01.570
that's if it's the board that makes those decisions. If you go as an individual and do something inappropriate,

00:54:01.810 --> 00:54:07.730
that may not cover it because it's the board that's protecting its members. And so if the board's doing something legit,

00:54:08.175 --> 00:54:09.455
you would be covered.

00:54:09.775 --> 00:54:15.135
I've seen board members learn about something in an executive session, go right out and blab about it, and then get sued.

00:54:15.775 --> 00:54:18.255
Those are the kinds of things you have to be incredibly

00:54:18.255 --> 00:54:21.615
careful about. Respect the need for confidentiality.

00:54:21.695 --> 00:54:24.870
You're in executive session, and something is told to you,

00:54:25.270 --> 00:54:27.350
you don't repeat it to anybody.

00:54:27.670 --> 00:54:32.950
I can remember one night, very contentious meeting. I think it was revolving around our superintendent search.

00:54:33.270 --> 00:54:38.550
And I came home 02:00 in the morning, and I was just furr, fired up and angry, and my

00:54:52.610 --> 00:54:59.810
Next day, she's in the supermarket. The biggest mouth on the town council happens to see her at the supermarket. Hey. So what happened to the meeting last night? And she told her.

00:55:01.170 --> 00:55:03.170
I never made that mistake again.

00:55:03.250 --> 00:55:04.210
>> Of course, it

00:55:05.645 --> 00:55:09.165
didn't make her happy. I can't talk to you about this stuff anymore. You glad.

00:55:10.045 --> 00:55:10.925
So

00:55:11.885 --> 00:55:14.365
it's really important to respect

00:55:14.365 --> 00:55:15.645
confidentiality

00:55:16.285 --> 00:55:24.150
and if acts are not wanton, reckless, or malicious. So if there can be like, that board member in that hearing. Let's say that was a termination,

00:55:24.390 --> 00:55:28.790
and he's on that hearing panel, and the let's say that attorney said,

00:55:29.110 --> 00:55:37.485
you said this was the worst teacher your child ever had. Right? How can you stand there and judge him? You didn't you're you came into this meeting with prejudice. You have

00:55:37.645 --> 00:55:38.925
a preconceived idea.

00:55:39.405 --> 00:55:49.630
It might get thrown out. So it's always really important to play by the rules and understand them. If you ever have a question, I would start maybe with a call to the court chair,

00:55:50.270 --> 00:55:51.390
the superintendent.

00:55:51.390 --> 00:55:58.350
We have attorneys at CABE. You're more than happy to call us. That's a free call. You're a member, so that's all part of the service.

00:55:58.750 --> 00:56:06.175
What would happen if, you know, we don't represent you in court, but we have experts on and I answer the phone every day.

00:56:06.575 --> 00:56:08.335
Really, I can answer that stuff too.

